    <StatementCodes>
      <StatementCode>CCSS.Math.Content.5.MD.C.5a</StatementCode>
    </StatementCodes>
    <Statements>
      <Statement>Find the volume of a right rectangular prism with whole-number side lengths by packing it with unit cubes, and show that the volume is the same as would be found by multiplying the edge lengths, equivalently by multiplying the height by the area of the base. Represent threefold whole-number products as volumes, e.g., to represent the associative property of multiplication.</Statement>
